        <p>The East Fjords offer Iceland's most remote and least visited region, where dramatic mountains rise directly from the sea and small fishing villages maintain traditional Icelandic culture. This region requires more time due to winding coastal roads, but rewards visitors with solitude and stunning scenery.</p>

